@page "/help/voice"

<div class="help-content">
    <h1><i class="fas fa-volume-up"></i> Voice Features (Text-to-Speech)</h1>
    
    <div class="help-section">
        <h2>What is Text-to-Speech (TTS)?</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Text-to-Speech</strong> reads important messages and announcements aloud, making the application 
            more accessible for users with visual impairments or those who prefer audio feedback.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="help-section">
        <h2>No Setup Required!</h2>
        <div class="alert alert-success">
            <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
            <strong>Ready to Use:</strong> Voice features work immediately using your browser's built-in 
            speech synthesis. No installation or configuration needed!
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="help-section">
        <h2>Enabling Voice Features</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to <strong>Settings ? Accessibility</strong></li>
            <li>Toggle <strong>"Enable Text-to-Speech"</strong> ON</li>
            <li>Adjust speech rate if desired (0.5x to 2.0x)</li>
            <li>Click <kbd>Speak</kbd> to test</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="help-section">
        <h2>What Gets Announced</h2>
        
        <h3>Automatic Announcements:</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>
                <i class="fas fa-dollar-sign text-success"></i>
                <strong>Transaction Saved:</strong>
                "Transaction saved. [Description] for $[Amount]"
            </li>
            <li>
                <i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle text-danger"></i>
                <strong>Validation Errors:</strong>
                "Error: [Error message]"
            </li>
            <li>
                <i class="fas fa-file-pdf text-info"></i>
                <strong>Report Generated:</strong>
                "Report generated: [Report name]"
            </li>
            <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-success"></i>
                <strong>Success Messages:</strong>
                Confirms completed actions
            </li>
            <li>
                <i class="fas fa-text-recognition text-primary"></i>
                <strong>OCR Complete:</strong>
                "Text extraction complete"
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="help-section">
        <h2>Keyboard Shortcuts</h2>
        <table class="table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Action</th>
                    <th>Shortcut</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Toggle TTS On/Off</td>
                    <td><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>S</kbd></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Stop Speaking</td>
                    <td><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>X</kbd></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <div class="help-section">
        <h2>Adjusting Speech Settings</h2>
        
        <h3>Speech Rate:</h3>
        <p>Control how fast text is spoken:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>0.5x:</strong> Slower (easier to understand)</li>
            <li><strong>1.0x:</strong> Normal speed (default)</li>
            <li><strong>1.5x:</strong> Faster</li>
            <li><strong>2.0x:</strong> Very fast</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="tip-box">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Adjust the speed in Settings ? Accessibility until you find a comfortable pace.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="help-section">
        <h2>Manual Text-to-Speech</h2>
        <p>In certain areas, you can manually trigger speech:</p>
        
        <h3>OCR Results:</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Extract text from an image using OCR</li>
            <li>Click <kbd><i class="fas fa-volume-up"></i> Read Aloud</kbd></li>
            <li>System reads the extracted text</li>
            <li>Click <kbd><i class="fas fa-stop"></i> Stop</kbd> to interrupt</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

